The paper deals with the construction of optimal cyclic codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The codes have applications in consumer electronics, data storage systems, and communication systems, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of coding theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of monomials, which are a topic in algebraic geometry and algebraic coding theory, making the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and symbolic computation (cs.SI) relevant as well.
